Summary: This is something I spotted on Google Maps (see attached). The URL: http://maps.google.com/?ie=UTF8&ll=53.835388,-3.029963&spn=0.001075,0.002119&t=h&z=19
divs: sighting detailsi do not believe this to be bad pixels in the data set since the outlines of this object(s) are blurred just like the adjacent objects on the ground. there is what seems to be four centers of light that are positioned in (i think some ways above) the shadow of a tree located on the side of the train station. also, this object(s) is position on (over) the railway tracks where there is no rail traffic at the time and hence no ground object to produce this effect. i do not know of a way where the time\date of this image can be obtained from google\tele atlas. i have not seen anything like this elswhere in the google maps data base, so i do not think it is an artifact of the imaging system that took the photograph. the only logical explanation i can think of is an aircraft, but this does not look like an aircraft.
